    • Method Detail

      • generateNumbers

        public static java.lang.String generateNumbers()
        Returns a String containing 6 random SuperLotto lottery numbers. The first 5 numbers are random numbers from the range 1 to 47, and the 6th number (the MEGA) is from 1 to 27. There are no duplicate numbers in the first 5 numbers of a string.
        Returns:
        a String with SuperLotto lottery number.

      • isDuplicate

        public static boolean isDuplicate(int newNum,
                                  int[] lotteryNumbers,
                                  int currIndexFilledArray)
        Checks whether the newly generated random number(newNum) is duplicate or not before adding it into the lotteryNumbers array.
        Parameters:
        newNum - the newly generated random number.
        lotteryNumbers - the array reference variable for lotteryNumbers array.
        currIndexFilledArray - is array index for lotteryNumbers array.
        Returns:
        a boolean value is the answer for whether newly generated random number is duplicate or not.

      • printTicket

        public static void printTicket(java.lang.String lottoNumString)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        Method appends a string in a file lottery.txt using write() and closes a FileWriter. Throws IOException if write() operation fails or close() operation fails or file not created.
        Parameters:
        lottoNumString - represents a String with SuperLotto lottery number.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Method throws exception if there is an issue with creation of a lottery.txt file or writing to the file or closing the file.
